@node INSTALL "WindChime: Installation."
You've obviously managed to unarchive the archive since you're reading this.

Drag the WindChime icon to where ever you want to run it from. There are two
other files, that do not have icons. They are "Chime" and "Water". You need to
copy them to the same directory too. Copy the source and documentation to
wherever you want to too.
@endnode

@node USAGE "WindChime: Usage."
After double-clicking on the WindChime icon a small window will open at the top
left of your screen. I don't have documentation on how to make the window font
sensitive, but as there is no text in the window, this is only a small issue.

The program changes the size of it's window immediately after opening. This is
done so that the gadgets are correctly placed with regard to the height of the
top border. I could find no other way of doing that with V1.3 includes.

The top slider alters the volume of the chime and the water. (The water is always
slightly quieter than the chime as you don't want to be running to the
bathroom every ten minutes =)

The bottom slider is the "windiness". That is, if you move it to the left, the
wind increases to a gale and the virtual wind chime gets clanged more. (Be
careful not to put it to the extreme left as it'll blow all your key caps
off=)

Hit the close button to kill it off.
@endnode

@node HISTORY "WindChime: History"
This program is my own interpretation of an identically named program available
for Windoze machines. No reverse engineering, "borrowing" of source or technology
or any other despicable Microsoft-like behaviour was performed in creating
WindChime. I claim WindChime as all my own work, except where otherwise stated.
(Namely, the bit about EasySound.)

	V1.0 was conceived late one night whilst changing my twelve day old son's
	     nappy and wishing that I was in bed.

	V1.1 removed the bug than meant that it only worked when the Wind Chime
	     window was active. (So much for the INTUITICKS message.) As a
	     consequence the CPU load has gone through the roof.

	V1.2 added proportional gadgets for volume and windiness. >BURP<

	V1.3 added Delay() statment into main wait loop to reduce CPU load.
	     Removed bug that crashed the machine if it couldn't find
	     appropriate samples.

	V1.4 added additional background sample "Water".
@endnode

@node TODO "WindChime: To Do"
